                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 294/428a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-01-15T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 15, 1925—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>47. L–204 for Logan. Please have National Bank of Belgium wire Federal Reserve
                    Bank New York to “Release blocked account to order of Treasury of the United
                        States”.<note n="37" xml:id="d138fn37">See sec. B, art. 3, agreement of Jan.
                        14, 1925, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
